## Turbo Frames

Turbo Frames update specific parts of the page without reloading.

### Basic Usage

```erb
<!-- app/views/articles/index.html.erb -->
<div id="articles-page-container">
  <h1>Articles</h1>
  
  <!-- Turbo Frame wraps the articles list -->
  <%= turbo_frame_tag "articles-list" do %>
    <div id="articles-list-container">
      <%= render @articles %>
    </div>
    <%= link_to "Load More", articles_path(page: @next_page) %>
  <% end %>
</div>
```

### Frame Targeting

```erb
<!-- app/views/articles/_article.html.erb -->
<!-- Each article has its own frame -->
<%= turbo_frame_tag dom_id(article) do %>
  <article id="<%= "article-#{article.id}-card" %>">
    <h2><%= link_to article.title, article %></h2>
    <p><%= article.body.truncate(200) %></p>
    
    <!-- Edit link stays within frame -->
    <%= link_to "Edit", edit_article_path(article) %>
    
    <!-- Delete button breaks out of frame to update whole page -->
    <%= button_to "Delete", article_path(article),
        method: :delete,
        data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
  </article>
<% end %>
```

### Frame Swapping Between Pages

```erb
<!-- app/views/articles/show.html.erb -->
<div id="article-show-container">
  <!-- Frame with matching ID from index page -->
  <%= turbo_frame_tag dom_id(@article) do %>
    <article id="article-content">
      <h1><%= @article.title %></h1>
      <div><%= @article.body %></div>
      
      <!-- Clicking Edit loads edit form in same frame -->
      <%= link_to "Edit", edit_article_path(@article) %>
    </article>
  <% end %>
</div>

<!-- app/views/articles/edit.html.erb -->
<!-- Same frame ID - replaces content in place -->
<%= turbo_frame_tag dom_id(@article) do %>
  <div id="article-edit-form-container">
    <h1>Edit Article</h1>
    <%= render "form", article: @article %>
  </div>
<% end %>
```

### Lazy-Loading Frames

```erb
<!-- Load content on demand -->
<%= turbo_frame_tag "comments", src: article_comments_path(@article) do %>
  <p>Loading comments...</p>
<% end %>

<!-- When frame appears in viewport, it fetches content from src URL -->
```

### Turbo Frame Rules

**1. Matching Frame IDs**
- Frames with same ID on different pages swap content
- Use `dom_id(record)` for consistent IDs

**2. Breaking Out of Frames**
```erb
<!-- Update entire page instead of just frame -->
<%= link_to "View All", articles_path, data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>

<!-- Target a different frame -->
<%= link_to "Update Sidebar", path, data: { turbo_frame: "sidebar" } %>
```

**3. Frame Responses Must Include Frame**
```erb
<!-- Controller response must include matching frame tag -->
<%= turbo_frame_tag "articles-list" do %>
  <%= render @articles %>
<% end %>
```
